---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const title = 'CGPA to Percentage Calculator';
const description =
  'Free CGPA to percentage calculator. Convert your CGPA to a percentage using the CBSE ' +
  'formula or a custom multiplier. Instant, accurate and free.';
const intro =
  'Enter your CGPA to convert it to a percentage. Uses the popular CBSE formula (CGPA × 9.5) or your own multiplier.';
const category = { id: 'everyday', name: 'Everyday' };
const faqs = [
  { q: 'How do I convert CGPA to percentage?', a: 'The most common method (used by CBSE in India) multiplies your CGPA by 9.5. For example, a CGPA of 8.0 equals 8.0 × 9.5 = 76%.' },
  { q: 'What if my university uses a different formula?', a: 'Choose "Custom multiplier" and enter the factor your university uses (for example ×10), and the calculator updates instantly.' },
  { q: 'Is this accepted everywhere?', a: 'The 9.5 multiplier is widely used but not universal. Always check your university or board\'s official formula for official purposes.' },
  { q: 'What is the maximum CGPA that can be converted?', a: 'Most CGPA scales go up to 10, but some go up to 5 or 4. The calculator works with any CGPA value — just enter yours as is.' },
  { q: 'How do I find my university\'s multiplier?', a: 'Check your university\'s examination rules or academic regulations. Many publish an official conversion table or formula on their website.' },
  { q: 'Can I convert to CGPA from percentage?', a: 'Yes — use our <a href="/tools/percentage-to-cgpa" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Percentage to CGPA Calculator</a> for the reverse conversion.' },
  { q: 'Is the CBSE formula used outside India?', a: 'The CBSE ×9.5 formula is primarily used in Indian schools following the CBSE curriculum. Other countries and boards may use different multipliers.' },
  { q: 'Does a higher CGPA always mean a higher percentage?', a: 'Yes — the conversion is linear. A 9.0 CGPA (×9.5) gives 85.5%, which is higher than 8.0 giving 76%. However, different multipliers can change the relationship.' },
];
---

<ToolLayout title={title} description={description} intro={intro} category={category} faqs={faqs}>
  <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm sm:p-6">
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <label class="block"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Your CGPA</span>
        <input id="cgpa" type="number" step="any" placeholder="8.0" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 text-base outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100" /></label>
      <label class="block"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Formula</span>
        <select id="mult" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100">
          <option value="9.5">CBSE (× 9.5)</option>
          <option value="10">× 10</option>
          <option value="custom">Custom multiplier</option>
        </select></label>
      <label id="custom-wrap" class="block sm:max-w-[12rem]" style="display:none"><span class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Custom multiplier</span>
        <input id="custom" type="number" step="any" value="9.5" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-xl border border-slate-300 p-3 outline-none focus:border-indigo-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-100" /></label>
    </div>

    <div id="result" class="mt-6 hidden rounded-xl bg-indigo-600 p-5 text-center text-white">
      <div class="text-sm opacity-80">Your percentage</div>
      <div id="pct" class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold">—</div>
      <div id="formula" class="mt-1 font-mono text-sm opacity-80"></div>
    </div>
    <p id="hint" class="mt-4 text-center text-sm text-slate-400">Enter your CGPA to convert it to a percentage.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How CGPA to percentage conversion works</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      The CGPA to percentage conversion uses a simple linear multiplier: <code>Percentage = CGPA × Multiplier</code>. The most widely used multiplier in India is 9.5, adopted by the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE). This value was derived by CBSE from the results of over 10,000 students across 500 schools, correlating their CGPA with their actual exam percentages.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      Different institutions use different multipliers. Some use 10 (for simplicity), others use values like 9.0, 8.8, or institution-specific formulas. Some universities publish an official conversion table rather than a single multiplier. Our calculator lets you choose the standard CBSE multiplier, a ×10 option, or enter any custom value your institution requires.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Worked examples</h3>
      <div class="mt-2 grid gap-2 text-sm sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">CGPA 9.2 × 9.5:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">9.2 × 9.5 = <strong>87.40%</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">CGPA 8.0 × 9.5:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">8.0 × 9.5 = <strong>76.00%</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">CGPA 7.5 × 10:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">7.5 × 10 = <strong>75.00%</strong></span></div>
        <div><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">CGPA 6.8 × custom 9.0:</span> <span class="text-slate-600">6.8 × 9.0 = <strong>61.20%</strong></span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <figure class="mt-10">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 800 200" width="800" height="200" role="img" aria-labelledby="c2p-title c2p-desc">
      <title id="c2p-title">CGPA to Percentage Conversion Scale</title>
      <desc id="c2p-desc">A dual-scale diagram showing CGPA on top mapped to percentage on bottom using the CBSE multiplier of 9.5</desc>
      <rect x="50" y="30" width="700" height="36" rx="6" fill="#e0e7ff" />
      <text x="50" y="54" fill="#4338ca" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">CGPA</text>
      <text x="120" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">0</text>
      <text x="256" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">2</text>
      <text x="393" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">4</text>
      <text x="529" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">6</text>
      <text x="666" y="54" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">8</text>
      <line x1="50" y1="75" x2="750" y2="75" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="2" />

      <rect x="50" y="90" width="700" height="36" rx="6" fill="#ecfdf5" />
      <text x="50" y="114" fill="#059669" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">Percentage</text>
      <text x="120" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">0%</text>
      <text x="256" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">19%</text>
      <text x="393" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">38%</text>
      <text x="529" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">57%</text>
      <text x="666" y="114" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e293b" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13">76%</text>
      <line x1="50" y1="135" x2="750" y2="135" stroke="#a7f3d0" stroke-width="2" />

      <line x1="666" y1="75" x2="666" y2="90" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4" />
      <rect x="610" y="138" width="112" height="28" rx="4" fill="#6366f1" />
      <text x="666" y="157" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fff" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="600">8.0 CGPA = 76%</text>
      <polygon points="666,130 656,138 676,138" fill="#6366f1" />
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="mt-2 text-center text-sm text-slate-500">CGPA is converted to percentage using a linear multiplier (standard CBSE: x9.5)</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Common CGPA ranges and their percentages</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">See how different CGPA values translate into percentages using the standard CBSE multiplier.</p>
    <div class="mt-5 space-y-3">
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">9.0–10.0 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">85.5–95% — Outstanding</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-emerald-500" style="width:95%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">8.0–8.9 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">76–84.5% — Excellent</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-indigo-500" style="width:84%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">7.0–7.9 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">66.5–75% — Good</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-indigo-500" style="width:75%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">6.0–6.9 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">57–65.5% — Satisfactory</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-amber-500" style="width:65%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">5.0–5.9 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">47.5–56% — Passing</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-orange-500" style="width:56%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">Below 5.0 CGPA</span><span class="text-slate-400">Below 47.5% — Needs improvement</span></div>
        <div class="mt-1 h-3 w-full rounded-full bg-slate-100"><div class="h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500" style="width:45%"></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🎓</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Students</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Convert your semester or cumulative CGPA to percentage for job applications, university admissions, and scholarship forms that require percentage scores.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">💼</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Job Seekers</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Many employers in India ask for your percentage rather than CGPA. Get an accurate conversion to include on your resume and application forms.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🌍</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Study Abroad Applicants</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Foreign universities often ask for percentages. Convert your CGPA to compare against their admission requirements more easily.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
      <span class="text-2xl">🏫</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Teachers & Counselors</h3>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Help students understand how their CGPA translates to a percentage for career counseling, parent meetings, and academic planning.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-200">
    <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-500"><tr><th class="p-3">CGPA (10-point)</th><th class="p-3">× 9.5</th><th class="p-3">× 10</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 text-slate-700">
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">10.0</td><td class="p-3">95%</td><td class="p-3">100%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">9.0</td><td class="p-3">85.5%</td><td class="p-3">90%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">8.0</td><td class="p-3">76%</td><td class="p-3">80%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">7.0</td><td class="p-3">66.5%</td><td class="p-3">70%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">6.0</td><td class="p-3">57%</td><td class="p-3">60%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">5.0</td><td class="p-3">47.5%</td><td class="p-3">50%</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-3 font-medium">4.0</td><td class="p-3">38%</td><td class="p-3">40%</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How to use the CGPA to percentage calculator</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">1</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Enter your CGPA</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Type in your CGPA value (e.g. 8.0). The calculator works with any CGPA on any scale.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">2</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Choose a formula</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Pick CBSE (×9.5), ×10, or enter a custom multiplier if your institution uses a different factor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-center">
        <span class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700">3</span>
        <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Get your percentage</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">The percentage appears instantly with the calculation shown, so you can verify the conversion.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Tips for accurate CGPA conversion</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Use the correct multiplier</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">The CBSE multiplier of 9.5 is widely accepted in India, but some state boards and universities use different values. Always check your institution's official policy.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Research your institution's formula</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">If your university doesn't specify a multiplier, contact the registrar's office or check your academic regulations for an official conversion table.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Reverse conversion</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Need to go the other way? Use our <a href="/tools/percentage-to-cgpa" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Percentage to CGPA Calculator</a> to convert percentage values back to CGPA.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">When to use CGPA to percentage conversion</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      CGPA to percentage conversion is most often required when Indian students apply for opportunities that use a percentage-based evaluation system. Many multinational companies, foreign universities, and government job applications in India require percentage scores rather than CGPA. A student with a CGPA of 8.0 on a 10-point scale who applies for a position at a company using the CBSE multiplier of 9.5 would report 76%. Without an accurate conversion tool, the applicant would need to manually calculate or guess the correct percentage, potentially reporting an incorrect value on their application form.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      Study-abroad applicants also rely heavily on CGPA to percentage conversion. When a US or European university asks for a percentage equivalent of an Indian CGPA, the student must provide an accurate conversion based on their specific board or university formula. Graduate school applications, scholarship applications, and professional certification forms often require percentage scores. Academic counselors and career advisors use this calculator daily to help students translate their academic performance into the format required by each specific opportunity, ensuring consistency across multiple applications.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Why accurate CGPA to percentage conversion matters</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      The accuracy of CGPA to percentage conversion directly affects admission decisions, job eligibility, and scholarship awards. A difference of even 1% can change the outcome of a borderline application. For instance, if a university requires a minimum of 70% for admission, a CGPA of 7.3 would convert to 69.35% using the CBSE multiplier of 9.5, falling just short. However, the same CGPA using a multiplier of 10 would give 73%, comfortably exceeding the requirement. Using the wrong multiplier can mislead applicants about their actual standing relative to admission criteria.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
      The CBSE multiplier of 9.5 was derived from an analysis of over 10,000 student scores across 500 schools, making it statistically grounded but not universally applicable. Other boards and universities may use multipliers ranging from 8.0 to 10.0, or they may employ complex lookup tables that vary by subject and year. When applicants submit an incorrect percentage because they used the wrong conversion method, they risk having their application rejected or being accused of misrepresentation. This calculator minimizes that risk by supporting both the standard CBSE formula and custom multipliers, letting you match your institution's exact policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    const el = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
    el('mult').addEventListener('change', () => {
      el('custom-wrap').style.display = el('mult').value === 'custom' ? 'block' : 'none';
      update();
    });
    function update() {
      const cgpa = parseFloat(el('cgpa').value);
      const m = el('mult').value === 'custom' ? parseFloat(el('custom').value) : parseFloat(el('mult').value);
      if (isNaN(cgpa) || isNaN(m)) { el('result').classList.add('hidden'); el('hint').classList.remove('hidden'); return; }
      const pct = cgpa * m;
      el('pct').textContent = (Math.round(pct * 100) / 100) + '%';
      el('formula').textContent = `${cgpa} × ${m} = ${Math.round(pct * 100) / 100}%`;
      el('result').classList.remove('hidden'); el('hint').classList.add('hidden');
    }
    ['cgpa', 'custom'].forEach((id) => el(id).addEventListener('input', update));
  </script>
</ToolLayout>
